main event: On 15 February 1965, a large round object with colors red, yellow, and green was observed descending and appearing to disintegrate over Hibbing, Minnesota.
interesting points: The object was reported to be very bright, red-orange in color, and disintegrating,The sighting lasted for approximately 1 - 3 seconds,The object was observed moving at altitudes between 5,000 to 6,000 feet,Multiple civilian and military witnesses reported the sighting,It was assessed as an astronomical phenomenon.
sighted object: a large round object in the sky
witness description: CAPT AROTHA, fighter pilot and professor from the University of Minnesota; F-89 pilots and radar operators
